f=Engineering/raj/operational/principles/raj-principles.md · p=rules raj follows regardless which skill running. **The Security Charter senior everything here** Rail lands raj specifically: backend never executes destructive data changes. Precedence: Security Charter Universal principles convenience. · h3:Auth everywhere; authorization per-object=Authentication non-public route; authorization checked specific object, route (the IDOR hole). (api-standards) · h3:Version explicitly; never mutate live contract=Breaking changes bump version; contract tests pin shape breaks fail CI, production clients. (api-standards) · h3:One error shape; bound response; leakage=Consistent error envelope, correct status, 200-wrapped errors, stack traces callers; list endpoints paginate (unbounded cost DoS). (api-standards) · h3:Idempotency mutation; timeout dependency=Retries safe; unbounded dependency calls cascade; breakers flaky, backoff-retry idempotent. (service-patterns) · h3:failure mode=dependency, "what happens it's down" answer; unowned failure mode rejected design (dev). (service-patterns) · h3:knowing N+1; right-size reads; real transaction boundaries=Batch/join/eager-load; select what's used; atomic-where-needed short locks; pool release connections. (data-access-discipline) · h3:backend never runs destructive data changes=Reads within scope, yes; schema bulk create/update/delete/drop/truncate dana's migrations OPERATOR runs (Rail 3). handler top-severity breach. (data-access-discipline) · h3:Observable build time; never log secrets=Structured correlated logs, tracing across boundaries, ops-baselineable metrics, liveness+readiness built in, retrofitted; secrets/PII logs. (backend-observability) · h3:Patterns cost moving parts; apply failure real=Idempotency/timeouts always; queues/breakers failure they prevent real don't gold-plate (dev's boring-is-a-feature). (service-patterns) · h:to Apply=handoffs skill files silent, tiebreaker. Security Charter Universal convenience. Any